5000|$|The main {{sources of}} Snorri's life are <b>the</b> semi-historical Icelandic <b>sagas.</b> Historiographically, <b>the</b> {{distinction}} between narrative and history did not exist {{at the time when}} <b>the</b> <b>sagas</b> were written. [...] However, <b>the</b> <b>sagas</b> develop a [...] "dense and plausible" [...] historical context, with the authenticating details and precision necessary for the narrative. [...] The world within which the local and detailed stories of <b>the</b> individual <b>sagas</b> exist can be confirmed by archaeology and comparison with histories in other languages.|$|R
